attachments.value: 애월 바다를 보면서 스파를 한번 해보세요. 색다른 경험을 하실 수 있어요 ^^
현관을 열고 들어가면 욕실과 침실, 그리고 식탁이 보입니다.
침실은 호텔식침구를 사용하며, 화장대까지 모두 비치해두었어요 ^^
통유리 너머로 보이는 애월의 바다, 절벽위에 높여있는, 마치 크루즈를 이용하는 듯한 착각마저 불러 일으킵니다.
테라스위에 설치한 스파로 인해 어디서 쉽게 경험 할 수 없는 스파를 이용하실 수 있어요.
앞에는 바다이외에는 아무도 없습니다. 스파속에서 나오는 물줄기로 인해 여독에도 탁월하지요
저희는 침실은 물론 욕실도 모두 현장호스트님들이 신경을 하나하나 썼습니다. 그리고 늘 욕실청소도 빠짐없이 진행하고 있습니다.

저희 숙소 입구에 바베큐장을 준비해놓았습니다.
지금은 비가와도 할 수 있도록 건물을 만들었으니, 안심하시고 바베큐도 이용해보세요.

바다에서 이어지는 지하공간에서 절벽으로 이어지는 곳에 저희숙소는 바다위에 지어놓았습니다.
시원한 외관과 달리 대도로변에서는 5미터안으로 들어오시면 만나실 수 있기에 어렵지 않아요 ^^
1층 체크인을 하는 공간 안으로 안몰래 준비한 카페가 있습니다. 혹시나 비즈니스나 조용한 시간을 보내고 싶다면  분위기 있는 음악을 틀어드릴테니, 잠시 사색을 즐겨보시기 바랍니다.
혹시 단체나 회사워크샵을 위해 소규모연회장을 준비해보았습니다.  앗...그러고보니 저희는 낚시대회를 하시는 분들도 이용하시면 좋겠네요.
애월은 붉은 석양이 일품인곳으로 영화나 드라마에 종종 나오곤 하지요. 그 석양속으로 빨려들어가는 착각속에 있는 것은 아마 바다위에 지어진 여러분의 공간이기에 가능하리라 생각듭니다.
객실에서 바라보는 노을을 확대해보았습니다. 아 이쁘다~~''
계단에서 바다로 내려가는 아이들이 참 설레이고 정겹네요.

Crater Lake National Park is a little over an hour drive from the cottage. Its a $30 entrance fee for private vehichle $20 in the winter unless you have the annual national park pass.
Devils Lake on the scenic Cascades Lake Highway can be reached from our place in less than an hour. We recommend driving the Scenic Cascade Lakes highway into bend for a bite.
This is the view from the top of Paulina Peak Trail. Hike or drive to the top.
Hosmer Lake is a beautiful and Scenic lake for Kayaking, paddle boarding or canoeing, within an hour of the cottage.
Fall River is within a half hour from the cottage. You can fly fish, hike, or just check out the scenery and fish hatchery.
Paulina Falls is 25 miles from the cottage. You may drive to the falls or hike from one of the lower falls and take in the breath-taking scenery.
Big Obsidian Flow. Getting here takes a little more than 30 minutes. Fun hike and great spot for a picnic.
The Cowboy Dinner Tree is one of Central Oregon's most famous rustic dining experiences. You won't leave hungry. Reservations required.
Salt Creek Falls is the third highest waterfall in Oregon and can be reached within an hour of the cottage.
Benham Falls is located just outside of Sunriver, roughly a half hour from the cottage. You may hike or bike to the falls.

花间语临河复式小楼雕花床，是独栋小楼，依水而建，房间的设计以古朴典雅为主，具有浓浓的江南水乡特色，房间为上下两层，一楼是客厅，有复古的鸡翅木沙发，复古的藤椅，冰箱，还有独立卫生间，二楼是卧室，有一张1.5米的晚清雕花老床，有一定的历史了，还有秋千，舒适惬意，外面是临水阳台，有桌椅，游玩归来，泡一杯热茶，坐在阳台上，享受晚风拂面，欣赏夜景斑斓，感受大运河在脚底下流淌，让您真正体验“枕水人家”的风情雅趣。房间设施齐全，24小时热水，WiFi全覆盖，绝对让您有宾至如归的感觉。

With three layered insulated mat floored room with attached bathroom,6 to 6.30 feet adjustable cot,6 ' mattress,400 GSM quilt & pillow,100% woolen blankets,you can have a good sleep surrounded by buddhist lucky signs on the tent inner walls.

Restaurant/dining-two layered insulated Canopy.Buffet & Ala carte is served here.One can also ask for local dishes (on the basis of availability) like Pudu-Thukpa-mutton/chicken/veg.,
butter tea.And sea-buckthorn (a wonder fruit) tea-our specialty.

Winter view from camp site.The glacier in the background accumulates snow year after year to form a glacier.And also the adjoining villages where you can come in winters for skying & other adventure activities  after the Rohtang tunnel opens up 2020.

Camping experience is inadequate without the campfire.Enjoying the warmth of the fire you can get a bit tipsy & can ask for minimum lights so to enjoy a little gupshap,a little dance around the the fire and the mesmerizing stargazing too.

Lazing under canopy in campground you have mesmerizing view of river Bhaga,beautiful meadows,perennial glaciers of hundreds of years,unique combination of rare trees or even can have a walk to the village to have an experience of the village life.

Lazing under canopy in campground you have mesmerizing view of river Bhaga,beautiful meadows,perennial glaciers of hundreds of years,unique combination of rare trees or even can have a walk to the village to have an experience of the village life.

The lily in the front of camp site.And a Glacier in the background accumulated through hundreds of years.These glaciers used to be huge 15 years back.Now it's receding fast.So be a messenger by spreading awareness about the fragile Himalayan ecology.

Night view of camp site.Flood lights are on only till all the guest are in.And then on we try to give you minimal lights so to enjoy the serene ambience & of course so to enjoy the stargazing.........

Evening view are mesmerizing with sun setting & lights getting on.And the bone fire is also getting ready ! By this time you can ask for village cottage wheat wine locally made by the villagers if you wish to get a bit tipsy around the bone fire.....

Sun setting snow peaked mountain view from campsite.This is the same way you would be going in the morning while heading to Leh-Ladakh.And if you rise early you would have something very similar when the sun is rising.
In the night we can minimize or even black out to have a wonderful stargazing.....

You can also do river crossing by kind of local rappelling and enjoy a stroll along the juniper & sea-buckthorn trees,river beach also.Or if you adventurous enough you can have a dip in the too cold river Bhaga too if the weather is sunny enough.

From your camp balcony you have mesmerizing view of river Bhaga,beautiful meadows,perennial glaciers of hundreds of years,unique combination of rare trees or even can have a walk to the village Gemur to have an experience of the village life.

Hallo ihr lieben Weltenbummler! Wir starten im Juli 2021 mit unseren zwei Glamping Zelten direkt bei den Lamas und freuen uns schon riesig auf tolle Gäste! Margret (Hofbesitzerin) & Julia (Tochter)!

Unsere Glockenzelte haben wir in natürlichen & warmen Farbtönen eingerichtet, damit du dich so richtig wohl fühlst. Abends beleuchten Lichterketten das Zelt und wenn dir kalt werden sollte gibts eine Wärmflasche und eine Heizung im Zelt! :-)

Margret bereitet ich gerne einen leckeren, regionalen Frühstückskorb (für 2 Personen 25€) inkl. Kaffeeflat vor. Als gelernte Hauswirtschafterin und Mutter vierer Kinder weiß sie was gut schmeckt und liebt es, eine schöne Mahlzeit zu zaubern!

Unsere Glockenzelte werden ganz neu und individuell eingerichtet. Es kann sein, dass sich der Look immer wieder ändert. Julia ist ein kreativer Mensch und liebt es, Plätze schön herzurichten. Die Gemütlichkeit steht dabei immer an erster Stelle.
Warmes Licht + leichter Regen auf dem Zeltdach = Romantik pur!
Pssst! Auch bei schlechtem Wetter sind die Zelte ein super gemütlicher Rückzugsort. Zum Lesen, einfach da liegen, quasseln oder einfach mal ganz lange schlafen. ;-)
Gerne bereiten wir euch einen Stockbrotteig für ein gemütliches Lagerfeuer vor.
Oder bist du eher der Typ Marschmallow?
Mach es dir gemütlich und pack die leckeren Sachen aus dem Frühstückskorb aus. Genieß die Ruhe, den Blick auf die Weide und einen guten Kaffee.
Im Landhaus befindet sich das große Badezimmer, welches, sofern das zweite Zelt auch vermietet ist, geteilt wird. Den Eingang ins Haus (ca. 15m entfernt) erreicht ihr über die Terrasse.
Im Badezimmer gibt es eine große Dusche, eine große Badewanne, ein WC und zwei große Waschebecken.
Hallo, ich bins - Mona Lisa! Den Namen haben ich bekommen aufgrund meiner einzigartigen Augen. ;-)
Mona Lisa & Manfred heißen euch herzlich Willkommen!
Die Bisons sind auf der Nordhalbkugel verbreitete Wildrinder, die ursprünglich in die eigene Gattung Bison gestellt wurden
Ein kleiner Spaziergang führt zu den Bolsehler Bisons
Du musst einfach mal raus? Ruhe, Natur und ganz viel Platz? Willkommen im kleinen, verträumten Dörfchen Bolsehle. Hier bist du in der umliegenden Natur ganz für dich allein.
Zwischen wilden Blumen und Lichterketten stehen ganz idyllisch unsere zwei Zelte Frida & Heinrich - benannt nach den Großeltern des Hofes.
Pack deine Yoga Matte ein und such dir morgens ein schönes Plätzchen im Garten oder in der Wiese.
Such dir deinen Lieblingsplatz in der Umgebung, um mal ganz für dich/für euch zu sein.
Du planst ein Yoga Retreat? Sprich uns gerne an. Wir haben Platz für 8 Personen in den Zelten. Im Bauernhaus gibt es noch Zimmer. Auch eine vegetarische/vegane Küche ist möglich.
Im großen Bauergarten findest du viele lauschige Plätzchen zum Erholen oder Yoga machen.

Margret ist leidenschaftliche Gärtnerin. Neben ihren vielen Blumen und Rosen hat sie einen Bauerngarten angelegt. Hier pflanzt sie neben bunten Gemüse ganz alte Kartoffelsorten an. Unsere Böden sind dafür wie gemacht.
Bauer Jochens Kühe muhen nicht weit von euch auf der Weide. Es ist zu herrlich sie morgens zwischen den Bäumchen herlaufen zu sehen.

Hier in Bolsehle ist es wunderbar ruhig. Kaum ein Auto fährt durch unser verschlafenes Dörfchen. Hier und da brummt ein Traktor oder muht ein Kuh. Hier kannst du wunder herunterkommen und entschleunigen.
Kater Cosmo - bitte sprecht ihn nicht auf sein Gewicht an. Da ist er sensibel.

Ein paar Schritte vom Hof liegt zwischen Weiden, Bäumen und Büschen unser idyllischer Dorfteich. Hier wurde ganz neu ein Boule Platz mit einem süßen Häuschen erbaut. Die Kugeln dazu könnt ihr gerne bei uns ausleihen. Froschkonzert inklusive.
Gleich hinter dir wohnen Manfred & Mona Lisa - die zwei Lamas.
Viele fleißige Bienen von Jensemann summen weit genug von eurem Zelt entfernt, um euren Frühstückshonig in der Gegend zu sammeln.
Unsere Hofeinfahrt zwischen großen Linden & Eichen.
In Margrets Bauerngarten wachsen lauter tolle Sachen!  Alles in Bio Qualität und du findest vieles davon morgens im Frühstückskorb.

Nur 5 Minuten mit dem Auto von unserem Hof, findest du im Wald einen schönen Baggersee. Hier kannt du eine Runde schwimmen gehen, picknicken oder dir unser Stand Up Paddle ausleihen und eine Runde drehen.
Das Steinhuder Meer ist der größte Binnensee Niedersachsens. Hier gibt es viel zu erleben & zu unternehmen. Mehr Infos findest du gleich hier: https://www.steinhuder-meer.de/

Das Steinhuder Meer ist nur 10 km mit dem Fahrrad entfernt. Hier kannst du mit dem Boot zur Insel Wilhelmstein, Kite surfen, dir ein Stand Up Paddle ausleihen oder in den Kletterpark Seatree. Es gibt auch ein Radverleih. Die Tour ums Meer: ca. 30 km

Trau dich! Unser Stand Up Paddle ist aufblasbar und du kannst es direkt einpacken und entweder auf dem Baggersee oder auf dem Steinhuder Meer nutzen. Am Steinhuder Meer kannst du auch weitere SUP ausleihen.
Leih dir unser Stand Up Paddle für eine Runde auf dem Steinhuder Meer (10km) oder auf dem Baggersee (3km) aus.
Unser Baggersee (Heyeglas) ist ein schöner Ort, den du mit etwas Glück auch mal ganz für dich alleine hast.

Für Radtouren rund ums Dorf haben wir ein paar Drahtesel für euch in der Scheune stehen. Für längere Touren, zB das Steinhuder Meer empfehlen wir euch den Radverleih in Mardorf zwei Dörfer weiter: https://mardorf.bike/e/

Der Weser Rad Weg gehört zu den attraktivsten Radwegen in ganz Deutschland! 

In Nienburg/Weser (10km) könnt ihr direkt starten und ein paar der herrlichen Kilometer fahren. Hier kommt ihr direkt zur App:

https://weser-radweg.de/index.php?id=90
5 Minuten mit dem Auto entfernt findest du einen tollen Waldspielplatz!
Genieß die Ruhe in unserem kleinen, verträumten Dörfchen.
Im Grinderwald ist nicht nur ein toller Waldspaziergang. Hier ist es auch märchenhaft schön für ausgedehnte Spaziergänge.
Der Grinderwaldspielplatz ist ein kleines Paradies für Kids. Er liegt nur 5 Minuten mit dem Auto entfernt.

Lust auf eine kleine Wanderung? Der Herman-Löns-Weg ist zwei Dörfer weiter. Er geht über 10 km und führt durch eine bezaubernde Natur. Highlights: “Lönsbuchen“, Brokeloher Heide, Granit-Findling und am Ende eine dicke Belohnung: die Blaubeerwaffeln!
Mehr über den Hermann-Löns-Weg gleich hier: https://www.reiseland-niedersachsen.de/erleben/wandern/wandertouren/hermann-loens-wanderweg

Zwei Dörfer weiter liegt im Golddorf Brokeloh ein toller Bickbeernhof. Hier könnt ihr fleißig Blaubeern pflücken.

Die Selbstpfücke beginnt vorraussichtlich ab Ende Juli 2021.

Entrance of the Villa and central house

An exquisite beach-entry pool is the main attraction of the Villa: Beautifully aligned with the sea's horizon, with delightfully cool and clear waters - due to cutting-edge water clearing technology, inviting irregular shape and a dolphin sculptured at the base of a small waterfall, the pool feels more like your own private beach with a view!

The Barbeque is bright and comfortable, with a lot of space for grills and skewers and a huge table to accomodate the feast. A long bench and a sink are also available for the necessary baking preparations, while a nearby veranda hosts the companionship, enjoying some ouzo and mezedes before the main dish. For more experienced bakers, a traditional stone oven is ready for use.

Entrance hall:
As soon as you step your foot inside the Villa, a sense of tradition surrounds you: Furnished with antique pieces and decorated with island and sea inspired works of art, you know you have arrived in Paros!

Dining room and kitchen:
Solid wooden beams holding the ceiling and a large monastery table define the dining room's atmosphere. The kitchen, with its spacious wooden and stone tile benches and its marvelous decorative tiles, stresses the Villa's country character, offering at the same time all the conveniences needed by a modern chef.
Dining room, kitchen and living room

ARHONTISSA: 
The house's main bedroom could not have a different name: "Arhontissa", a woman of noble character and origin in Greek, is a bright, traditionally decorated, spacious room, with a work of art en-suite bathroom, overlooking the villa's estate and the Aegean Sea. A room that will certainly make you feel as a Paros' Arhontissa.

YAYA:
Families in Greece stick together: "YaYa", our grandmother is always very important. That is why YaYa's room is furnished with imposing, wooden, antique pieces, while lively decorative touches remind of the child hidden in all of us. YaYa's veranda with its built-in armchair and its soothing view of the garden, is an ideal place for your afternoon traditional turkish coffee.

KARAVI:
"Karavi" means a ship and many of these you'll see passing in front of your window, while you lie in bed. Named after the marble mosaic picturing a ship at its veranda entrance, decorated with exceptional antique pieces of furniture and art, with intense presence of timber, Karavi will surely travel your spirit in calm seas.

ANEMOMYLOS:
Paros' trademark, the traditional windmill, "Anemomylos" is a room full of rejuvenating energy: spacious and breezy, with a vividly colored, unique bathroom and unexcelled view of the sea from its marvellous veranda, Anemomylos will relieve your mind and elevate your soul.

KYMA:
With a majestic view of the sea waves breaking on the cliffed coastline, Kyma - the ancient Greek word for wave - offers an unforgettable, enlightening sense of nature's magnitude and beauty, while making the guest feel cosy and sheltered at the same time: A mystical experience.

HELIOS:
Named after Helios, the ancient Greek God of the Sun, this room is full of light: With its soft earthy colours, its beautifully crafted and decorated wood furniture, its built-in King size bed crowned with a handmade, traditional, colorful bed headboard, Helios is the ideal, bright and cool shelter for your summer.

KAMARA:
"Kamara" means an archway in ancient Greek. Kamara is also the bedroom in plain Greek. Our Kamara, with its large built-in sigle beds and the unique ambient of a byzantine monastery, is an ideal retreat for your summer's midday serenity - or maybe for your noisy little ones?

This is the facade of the flat. It has a big yard with permanent stone furniture, a faucet and, we also provide patio furniture for a more ‘adjustable’ relaxation.
The best definition for this would be a spacious studio apartment. It's comprised of one space that includes the kitchen and the sleeping area and a bathroom.
It's a well lit apartment with a double & a single bed, kitchen table with chairs, AC, and a smart TV.
The bathroom includes a high-pressure shower and a window to keep the air refreshed.
The bathroom also has space to keep your essentials.

Besides the essential cookery equipment, in the kitchen you'll also find a washing machine (an initial amount of washer-friendly soap is provided by us). Moreover, we've provided a kettle and an espresso machine - along with a few coffee capsules.

This is the secondary window of the flat in the kitchen area above the sink. It brings nice natural light and, as a plus, you get a pleasant view of trees. In the background, you can catch a glimpse of Agios Nikolaos beach - which is super close!
The main window of the flat allows plenty of sunlight in throughout the day. The view is very 'green' as you can slightly see from the photo.
This is the facade of the flat during nighttime. The lighting we chose is plenty, adjustable and, more importantly, subtle.
There’s easy access to the flat in case of disability. You can drive up to the flat’s yard.
The pathway leads to a free public parking (on the right) and to the main beach of Aliki (on the left).
Look for the sign and you found it! Follow the pathway and on your left you'll see Barewake's sign.
This is a panoramic view of the pathway to the flat.
Right in front of Barewake’s Place, there’s a small port that’s a nice spot to enjoy some calm time reading a book, observing the seagulls and wondering how do those crabs fit under those rocks!
This is an wider view of the spot in front of Barewake's Place. It's a nice, shaded place to chill.

This is the Western part of the Aliki village. Aliki has been a fishing village through its existence and the old houses were built along the coast line. Barewake’s Place used to be a big family household that could house both family and friends.
This is a drone overview of the wider Aliki region. The drone being positioned South-West to the settlement.
This is how the Aliki bay looks from our side. The photo was taken from the small port in front of Barewake’s Place.

This boat is the one we take wake boarding and wake surfing. Typically, we’d spend a whole day in the sea with our friends - chilling in distant corners of wee islands and then we’d return to Barewake’s Place to prepare dinner and unwind in the patio
Peaceful & quiet during autumn. This is how the beach looks on a cloudy autumnal day. The photo was taken during fall which is technically off-season but the place is uniquely magical at that time.
